Cell.Text: [S] So, it is done. Alduin dilon. The Eldest is no more, he who came before all others, and has always been.

Node.Caption: MQ306PaarthurnaxIntroTopic

Cell.Text: Happy? No, I am not happy. Zeymahi lost ont du'ul Bormahu. Alduin was once the crown of our father Akatosh's creation.

Node.Caption: MQ306PaarthurnaxIntroA1: You don't sound very happy about it.

Cell.Text: Of course. Alduin wahlaan daanii. I would not have helped you if I thought otherwise.

Node.Caption: MQ306PaarthurnaxIntroA2: I have no regrets. Alduin had to be destroyed.

Cell.Text: You did what was necessary. Alduin had flown far from the path of right action in his pahlok - in the arrogance of his power.

Node.Caption: MQ306PaarthurnaxIntroB1: It was necessary.

Cell.Text: Indeed. Alduin wahlaan daanii. | His doom was written when he claimed for himself the lordship that properly belongs to Bormahu - our father Akatosh.

Node.Caption: MQ306PaarthurnaxIntroA3: Alduin brought this on himself.

Cell.Text: But I cannot celebrate his fall. Zu'u tiiraaz ahst ok mah. He was my brother once. This world will never be the same.

Node.Caption: MQ306PaarthurnaxIntroB2

Cell.Text: And so you fulfilled your destiny, which you once said you did not believe in.

Node.Caption: MQ306PaarthurnaxIntroC1: I told you I'd stop him, and I did.

Cell.Text: You once told me you did not believe in destiny.
Indeed, you saw more clearly than I - certainly more clearly than Alduin. Rok funta koraav.

Node.Caption: MQ306PaarthurnaxIntroC2: I was just fulfilling my destiny as Dragonborn.

Cell.Text: Perhaps now you have some insight into the forces that shape the vennesetiid... the currents of Time. | Perhaps you begin to see the world as a dovah.

Node.Caption: MQ306PaarthurnaxIntroD2

Cell.Text: G|But I forget myself. Krosis. So los mid fahdon. Melancholy is an easy trap for a dovah to fall into. | You have won a mighty victory. Sahrot krongrah - one that will echo through all the ages of this world for those who have eyes to see. | Savor your triumph, Dovahkiin. This is not the last of what you will write upon the currents of Time.

Node.Caption: MQ306PaarthurnaxIntroD1

Cell.Text: Perhaps. At least it will continue to exist. Grik los lein. | And, as you told me once, the next world will have to take care of itself. Ful nii los. Even I cannot see past Time's ending.

I am glad you believe that. At least it will continue to exist. Grik los lein. | Even I cannot see past Time's ending to what comes next. Niid koraav zeim dinoksetiid. We must do the best we can with this world.

Node.Caption: MQ306PaarthurnaxIntroC3: The world is a better place without Alduin.

Cell.Text: GS|Pruzah wundunne wah Wuth Gein. I wish the old one luck in his... quest. | But I doubt many will wish to exchange Alduin's lordship for the tyranny of Paarthurnax's "Way of the Voice".
G|If Alduin himself could not stand against your thu'um, I feel no shame in my own defeat.

Node.Caption: MQ306OdahviingBlockingTopic

Cell.Text: I can see it in your eyes - you've seen the land of the gods and returned.

Node.Caption: MQ306ArngeirBlockingTopic

Cell.Text: [S] Does this mean... is it done? Is Alduin truly defeated?

Node.Caption: MQ306ArngeirBlockingA1: Yes, I found Alduin's portal to Sovngarde.

Cell.Text: G|At last. It is over. Perhaps it was all worth it, in the end.

Node.Caption: MQ306ArngeirBlockingB1: Yes. I went to Sovngarde and killed Alduin there.

Cell.Text: G|Then it is done at last. Perhaps it was all worth it, in the end.

Node.Caption: MQ306ArngeirBlockingB2: As dead as I can make him.

Cell.Text: G|<<Shared>> Perhaps, perhaps not. Dragons are not like normal mortal creatures, and Alduin is unique even among dragonkind. | He may be permitted to return at the end of time to fulfill his destiny as the World-Eater. | But that is for the gods to decide. You have done your part.

Node.Caption: MQ306ArngeirBlockingB3: I hope so. But I don't know if Alduin can ever be completely destroyed.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Perhaps, perhaps not. Dragons are not like normal mortal creatures, and Alduin is unique even among dragonkind. | He may be permitted to return at the end of time to fulfill his destiny as the World-Eater. | But that is for the gods to decide. You have done your part.

Node.Caption: MQ306AlduinTopic: Is Alduin really dead? I didn't absorb his soul when he died.

Cell.Text: We heard the news from Whiterun - that you left the city on the back of a dragon! | That's a little... showy, even for you.
G|Please... Delphine has been very worried about you.

Node.Caption: MQ306BladesBlockingTopic

Cell.Text: Since you're still alive, I assume you have good news to report?

Node.Caption: MQ306DelphineA1

Cell.Text: [S] Gods above... that's better news than I had hoped! | When you walked into my inn that day, I never imagined where it would all lead... dragons out of legend... Sovngarde...

Node.Caption: MQ306DelphineB1: Yes. I used Alduin's portal to travel to Sovngarde. He's dead.
